One victim said the raiders are also forcing them to part with cash in case they sold their animals.Another villager narrated how she lost four cows to the raiders, saying the attackers also seriously injured her son. Residents of Maai Mahiu in Naivasha have appealed to law enforcers to  beef up security over increasing incidents of cattle raids in the area.
In the recent past, several residents have fallen victim to the cattle raiders, with those interviewed accusing the police of laxity.
A victim, Ann Wairimu, said the raiders are also forcing them to part with cash in case they sold their animals.



