"The raiders are roaming the village with impunity, stealing animals from villagers and our pleas to security agencies have fallen on deaf ears," she complained.
Another villager, Pauline Murugi, narrated how she lost four cows to the raiders, saying the attackers also seriously injured her son.
Ms Murugi said she has been forced to abandon cattle rearing after being attacked several times.
"I have lost animals to the attackers on several occasions and the law enforcers are not doing much to deal with the situation," she said.



