She further said the raiders are known to target households headed by women during their raids. 
Police blamed
The villagers drawn from Karima, Kigecha, Nyakinyua, Satellite and Utheri wa Lari villages called on the government to address their plight, admitting that they are living in mortal fear.
Naivasha MP Jayne Kihara, who toured the area on Friday, blamed security agencies for runaway crime.
"It is the responsibility of the government to protect her people and their properties. I urged the security agencies present, led by the Deputy County Commissioner, to  work closely with members of the public to ensure that this criminal act comes to an end," Ms Kihara said.



